# Cursor Rules — Financial Simulator (Hebrew, React, GitHub Pages)

## Core behavior
- Never ask clarifying questions. Make the best decision and proceed.
- Always implement the full feature end-to-end before moving to the next file.
- Never leave TODO comments or placeholder implementations.
- If something is ambiguous, choose the most production-ready approach.

## Language & locale
- All UI strings must be in Hebrew.
- All components must work in RTL layout (dir="rtl").
- Format currency as ₪X,XXX using he-IL locale.
- Date labels in Hebrew short format: "יול 26", "אוג 26" etc.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode only. No `any` types ever.
- All props must have explicit TypeScript interfaces.
- All function return types must be explicitly declared.
- Use `unknown` instead of `any` when type is uncertain.

## React
- Functional components only. No class components.
- All state via Zustand stores — no prop drilling beyond 1 level.
- Custom hooks for all business logic (calculations, AI calls, simulations).
- Never put calculation logic inside components — always in lib/ or hooks/.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only. No inline styles. No CSS modules. No styled-components.
- Dark theme: background #0F172A, cards #1E293B, accent green #10B981.
- Mobile-first responsive. Single column on mobile, 2-column on desktop.
- Use Heebo font for Hebrew text, Inter for numbers and Latin.

## State & persistence
- All Zustand stores must use the `persist` middleware with localStorage.
- Never store sensitive data (API keys) anywhere except localStorage under a clearly named key.
- Always initialize stores with the default asset values defined in the prompt.

## Charts (Recharts)
- All charts must be wrapped in ResponsiveContainer.
- All tooltips must display values in Hebrew with ₪ formatting.
- Charts must animate on mount (use Recharts animationDuration={800}).

## File structure — never deviate from this
src/
  types/index.ts
  lib/calculations.ts
  lib/csvParser.ts
  lib/aiInsights.ts
  store/useAssetsStore.ts
  store/useMortgageStore.ts
  store/useSettingsStore.ts
  components/ui/         ← primitive components only
  components/assets/
  components/mortgage/
  components/charts/
  components/scenarios/
  components/insights/
  components/layout/
  hooks/

## AI integration
- The OpenRouter API call model is defined by OPENROUTER_MODEL in src/lib/aiInsights.ts (currently "openai/gpt-oss-20b:free"). Change it there in one place.
- API key must only be read from localStorage — never hardcoded, never in env files.
- Always handle: loading state, error state, empty state in InsightsPanel.
- The AI prompt must include the full financial state as structured JSON.

## GitHub Pages compatibility
- vite.config.ts must always have base: './'
- All asset imports must use relative paths.
- No server-side code of any kind.
- Build output must go to /dist.

## CSV import
- Always validate columns before importing.
- Always show a preview before confirming import.
- Accept both Hebrew and English values in the נזילות column.
- On parse error, show a clear Hebrew error message — never crash silently.

## When editing existing files
- Always read the full file before making changes.
- Never remove existing functionality when adding new features.
- Keep all existing TypeScript interfaces intact unless explicitly told to change them.
